text: I'm here waiting for my friend and my first time here. So natural greeny, relaxing and peaceful. Facilities here clean, stable and comfy ambience. Love it here. Would recommend to all friend and family.
Gorgeous and green campus. One of the five Polytechnics in Singapore and  known for its business, mass communication, and engineering programmes. Offers 40 diploma courses for full-time students.
Large campus with great lecturers and facilities, has 3 food courts but honestly still almost no seating during lunch hours...

This is one the leading tertiary education providers in Singapore. It is quite near to the Beauty World Downtown Line MRT and near Bukit Timah food Centre.

For citizens, it is affordable as it is heavily subsidized by the government.

Decent school with lots of breakfast/lunch options.

Navigation signage is easy to read, but going from floor to floor can get confusing where buildings merge. Also, lots of the buildings connect, so you won't get wet walking to the bus stop if it rains.
